t-least-some-of-the-time" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Fast Company</a> )</p><p> • <strong>Investors</strong> <strong>Are Bailing on Cathie Wood&#39;s Popular ARK Fund</strong> : “Cathie Wood&#39;s flagship exchange-traded fund has rallied more than 50% this year. Investors are using that as an opportunity to get out. They have pulled a net $717 million from the ARK Innovation ETF over the past 12 months, according to FactSet. That exodus marks a notable shift for a fund that had consistently drawn investor cash since its 2014 inception. Once the largest actively managed ETF with nearly $30 billion in assets under management, the fund has shrunk to roughly $9 billion, mostly due to investment losses.” （ <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/investors-are-bailing-on-cathie-woods-popular-ark-fund-dbf5d801" target="_blank" rel="noopener">华尔街日报</a>）</p><p> • <strong>A New Job for Electric Vehicles: Powering Homes During Blackouts</strong> : Some energy experts say battery-powered vehicles will increasingly help keep the lights on and support electric grids, rather than straining them. ( <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2023/07/16/business/energy-environment/electric-vehicles-backup-power.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">New York Times</a> ) <em>see also</em> <strong>All the Ways to Slow a Car (Even Some Bad Ways)</strong> : Electric vehicles are increasingly popular, so it&#39;s time to talk about regenerative braking—and all the other ways you can stop a vehicle. ( <a href="https://www.wired.com/story/all-the-ways-to-slow-a-car-even-some-bad-ways/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Wired</a> )</p><p> • <strong>Here are all the positive environmental stories from 2023 so far</strong> We&#39;re going to be regularly updating this page with good news about our planet in an effort to combat climate anxiety. ( <a href="https://www.euronews.com/green/2023/07/11/here-are-all-the-positive-environmental-stories-from-2023-so-far" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Euro News</a> )</p><p> • <strong>What I Saw in Elon Musk&#39;s Truth Army</strong> : Twitter&#39;s “Community Notes” volunteers are supposed to make the platform “the most accurate source of information about the world.” I became one. ( <a href="https://slate.com/technology/2023/07/twitter-community-notes-elon-musk-fact-checking.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Slate</a> ) <em>see also</em> <strong>Here&#39;s How Twitter Could Become Irrelevant</strong> : Threads, from Instagram, has many distinct qualities that make it the first credible threat to Elon Musk&#39;s vision of what a social network should be. （ <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/heres-how-twitter-could-become-irrelevant-b2b027af" target="_blank" rel="noopener">华尔街日报</a>）</p><p> • <strong>Where Johnny Cash Came From</strong> : The Man in Black grew up in Dyess, Arkansas, in a community of poor farmers working government land. ( <a href="https://www.neh.gov/article/where-johnny-cash-came" target="_blank" rel="noopener">National Endowment for the Humantiies</a> )</p></blockquote><p>请务必与<a class="gtrackexternal" href="https://www.knighthead.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Knighthead Capital</a>联合投资组合经理 Tom Wagner 一起查看本周的<a href="https://ritholtz.com/category/podcast/mib/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" data-web-url="http://www.bloombergview.com/topics/masters-in-business">商业硕士课程</a>。这家价值 100 亿美元的事件驱动型投资者是一家深度关注价值的投资者，专门投资于需要财务和运营重组的公司。他与足球传奇人物汤姆·布雷迪 (Tom Brady) 共同投资了多项体育资产，包括<a class="gtrackexternal" href="https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2022-10-12/why-a-hedge-fund-manager-is-betting-on-pickleball-with-tom-brady#xj4y7vzkg" target="_blank" rel="noopener">匹克球队</a>、英格兰足球联赛的<a class="gtrackexternal" href="https://theathletic.com/4498330/2023/05/08/tom-wagner-birmingham-city/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">伯明翰城足球俱乐部</a>和耐力赛车队。瓦格纳的职业生涯始于安永会计师事务所，从事对冲基金会计工作。</p><p></p><p> <strong>These vehicles are the deadliest cars on the road, IIHS auto safety report says</strong><br /> <a href="https://ritholtz.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/deadliest.png" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone wp-image-316657" src="https://ritholtz.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/deadliest.png" alt="" width="600" height="517" srcset="https://ritholtz.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/deadliest.png 1352w, https://ritholtz.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/deadliest-300x258.png 300w, https://ritholtz.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/deadliest-1024x882.png 1024w, https://ritholtz.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/deadliest-768x661.png 768w, https://ritholtz.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/deadliest-250x215.png 250w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /></a><br /> Source: <a href="https://www.axios.com/2023/07/13/deadliest-cars-suvs-pickups-auto-safety-iihs" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Axios</a></p><p></p><div><div class="pf-content"><p> <a class="gtrackexternal" href="https://mailchi.mp/005fb77d75b9/ritholtzreads" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><em>在此注册我们的只读邮件列表</em></a>。</p><p></p></div></div><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://ritholtz.com/2023/07/10-tuesday-am-reads-434/">10 Tuesday AM Reads</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://ritholtz.com">The Big Picture</a> .</p> ;
如何在市场上致富https://ritholtz.com/2023/07/how-to-get-rich-in-the-markets/Barry Ritholtz Mon, 17 Jul 2023 13:00:02 +0000 Behavioral Finance/PsychologyInvestingReally, really bad calls https://ritholtz.com/?p=316701 <p>钱使世界运转。全球资本市场（股票、债券、私人投资、房地产）价值超过 100 万亿美元。如果你想变得富有，就去有钱的地方。 If you are smart, and understand how to play this, your odds of amassing a small fortune will go up dramatically. But a…</p><p><a class="button" href="https://ritholtz.com/2023/07/how-to-get-rich-in-the-markets/">阅读更多<i class="icon ion-arrow-right-c"></i></a></p><p><a rel="nofollow" href="https://ritholtz.com/2023/07/how-to-get-rich-in-the-markets/">《如何在市场致富》</a>一文首先出现在<a rel="nofollow" href="https://ritholtz.com">《The Big Picture》</a>上。</p> ; <p> <a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Wooing_the_Wealthy_Widow_-_The_Mascot,_New_Orleans,_1895.jpg" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone wp-image-316704" src="https://ritholtz.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Wooing_the_Wealthy_Widow_-_The_Mascot_New_Orleans_1895.jpg" alt="" width="720" height="479" srcset="https://ritholtz.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Wooing_the_Wealthy_Widow_-_The_Mascot_New_Orleans_1895.jpg 987w, https://ritholtz.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Wooing_the_Wealthy_Widow_-_The_Mascot_New_Orleans_1895-300x199.jpg 300w, https://ritholtz.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Wooing_the_Wealthy_Widow_-_The_Mascot_New_Orleans_1895-768x510.jpg 768w, https://ritholtz.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Wooing_the_Wealthy_Widow_-_The_Mascot_New_Orleans_1895-250x166.jpg 250w" sizes="(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px" /></a></p><p></p><p>钱使世界运转。全球资本市场（股票、债券、私人投资、房地产）价值超过 100 万亿美元。如果你想变得富有，就去有钱的地方。</p><p> If you are smart, and understand how to play this, your odds of amassing a small fortune will go up dramatically.</p><p>但很多人的做法都是错误的； some never achieve their goals, and others get there too late. Still, others take shortcuts, which can lead to profit disgorgement, lifetime bannings – even jail.</p><p> If you want to get rich in the markets, there are a few things that are crucial to understand. These are not secrets, they are just <em>Truths</em> that very few people will divulge to you. But I&#39;m going to share the ten ways I know where you can score big — <em>really big</em> ! — in the markets.</p><p>转折？ They are ranked here based on three factors:</p><blockquote><p> 1) Degree of difficulty;<br /> 2）成功的可能性；和<br />3) Time needed to amass a fortune.</p></blockquote><p>我从最难/最不可能成功到最简单/最有可能积累财富的方法来介绍它们：</p><p>让我们致富吧：</p><p> 1. <strong><u>Find the Next Apple or Nvidia or whatever</u></strong> : What could be easier?找到一家不受欢迎、未被发现、被低估的小公司，然后<em>买买买</em>！周围有很多创新者，您所需要做的就是发现他们！然后，说服许多其他人也这样做（在你已经拥有它们之后）。</p><p> Oh, and then the hard part: Hold them until the rest of the world figures out what you already know.最终，这些未被发现的宝石将获得巨大的增长和利润，其股价将飙升！</p><p> –<em>难度</em>：10/10<br /> –<em>成功的可能性</em>：1/10<br /> – <em>Time Required</em> : 5-20 years</p><p> 2.<strong><u>创新</u></strong>：在过去的几十年里，市场出现了巨大的创新。 Whether it&#39;s ETFs, Direct Indexing, free trading apps, private credit, cryptocurrencies, or any manner of FinTech ideas, the world of investing has become rife with clever new ways to do it faster/cheaper/better than ever before.</p><p>您所需要做的就是发明其中之一，围绕您的创新建立一家公司，将其货币化，然后出售给一家更大的公司。 What&#39;s so hard about that?</p><p> –<em>难度</em>：9/10<br /> –<em>成功的可能性</em>：2/10<br /> –<em>所需时间</em>：2-7年</p><p>3. <strong><u>Jump on the next bubble (but jump off before it pops)</u></strong> : There are bubbles everywhere, and to profit from them, you only need to do four things: 1. Identify these bubbles as they ramp up; 2. Buy into them (even if pricey); 3. Figure out when they are about to peak; 4. Sell your holdings before the collapse. ( <em>See also</em> : Trade options)</p><p> –<em>难度</em>：8/10<br /> –<em>成功的可能性</em>：3/10<br /> –<em>所需时间</em>：1-5年</p><p>4. <strong><u>Short Stocks/Markets</u></strong> : The flip side of bubble trading is to identify wildly overvalued companies or markets, and then bet against them. Sure, the crowd is right most of the time, but when they are wrong, it&#39;s spectacular.</p><p> You will need a steel gut to deal with the short squeezes and vitriol that come your way, but surely it&#39;s worth it. You can also score bonus points for identifying the frauds the regulators miss.</p><p> –<em>难度</em>：7/10<br /> –<em>成功的可能性</em>：4/10<br /> –<em>所需时间</em>：6个月至3年</p><p>5.<strong><u>把握市场时机</u></strong>：市场上涨，市场下跌，站在趋势的正确一边有多难？</p><p> –<em>难度</em>：6/10<br /> –<em>成功的可能性</em>：5/10<br /> –<em>所需时间</em>：每当下一个重大逆转发生时</p><p>6.<strong><u>提供有价值的服务</u></strong>：现在我们要做一些繁重的工作。找出一种提供某种服务的方法，无论是研究、执行还是资产管理，甚至只是简单地识别其他人都错过的事情。然后您所要做的就是通过该服务获利。</p><p> –<em>难度</em>：8/10<br /> –<em>成功的可能性</em>：7/10<br /> –<em>所需时间</em>：7-12年</p><p>7.<strong><u>成为一名出色的推销员</u></strong>：如果你能让人们购买你所销售的任何产品，并对该产品收取大量的加价和/或佣金或费用，那么你就可以在这项业务中大赚一笔。您甚至不必是正确的，您只需要充满信心并赢得客户的信任即可。我从来都不是一个优秀的推销员，但我总是对那些优秀的推销员心存敬畏。</p><p> –<em>难度</em>：5/10<br /> –<em>成功的可能性</em>：9/10<br /> –<em>所需时间</em>：开始关闭需要多长时间</p><p>8.<strong><u>指数</u></strong>：买入整个市场；持有多年；享受你的退休生活。</p><p> The challenge is that your own instincts and behavior will work against you the whole time.</p><p> While this should be a 1 out of 10 in terms of degree of difficulty, unfortunately, your own wetware makes it harder than it should be.</p><p> –<em>难度</em>：5/10<br /> –<em>成功的可能性</em>：10/10<br /> –<em>所需时间</em>：20-50年</p><p>9. <strong><u>Dollar Cost Average</u></strong> : DCA is yet another way to all but guarantee to accumulate a fortune, but only if you stick to it over time. Doing this with indexes or broad markets is the preferred way but it&#39;s been done successfully with individual stocks (primarily blue chips).</p><p> –<em>难度</em>：3/10<br /> –<em>成功的可能性</em>：9/10<br /> –<em>所需时间</em>：10-50年</p><p>10.<strong><u>永远复利（又名很少出售）</u></strong> ：时间是你在市场上的朋友，你的投资复利时间越长，特别是如果你再投资股息或利息，你的境况就会越好。嘿，如果这对沃伦·巴菲特来说足够好，那么对你来说也足够好。</p><p> –<em>难度</em>：2/10<br /> –<em>成功的可能性</em>：10/10<br /> –<em>所需时间</em>：永远</p><p style="text-align: center;">~~~</p><p>投资者面临着无穷无尽的选择，但这一切都归结为：你想以简单的方式做到这一点，还是以困难的方式做到这一点？你所要做的就是有足够的耐心，慢慢致富。</p><p></p><p></p><p><em>以前</em>：<br /><a href="https://ritholtz.com/2023/01/simple-but-hard/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">简单但困难</a>（2023 年 1 月 30 日）</p><p> <a href="https://ritholtz.com/2023/03/how-many-bear-markets-have-you-lived-through/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">您经历过多少次熊市？</a> （2023 年 3 月 3 日）</p><p><a href="https://ritholtz.com/2022/01/problem-solving-exercise/">投资是一种解决问题的练习</a>（2022 年 1 月 31 日）</p><p><a href="https://ritholtz.com/2020/01/bbrg-shunning-new-cars/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">没有人会因为拒绝新车和拿铁咖啡而致富</a>（2020 年 1 月 13 日）</p><p></p><p> <a rel="nofollow" href="https://ritholtz.com/2023/07/how-to-get-rich-in-the-markets/">《如何在市场致富》</a>一文首先出现在<a rel="nofollow" href="https://ritholtz.com">《The Big Picture》</a>上。</p> ;
